{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Fluid Sim 2D",
  "description": "Density-displacement particle compute fluid simulation — atom-decomposed from the bundled `fluid_seed` + `fluid_simulate` + `fluid_gradient_rotate` primitives into the curated library.\n\nPer-frame pipeline:\n1. **Seed branch** (open family — pattern math is JSON-editable WGSL): `wgsl_compute(seed_pattern_density)` writes a single-channel density Texture2D selecting one of 7 patterns (cluster / h-lines / v-lines / rings / cross / spiral / edge-ring) via `pattern` uniform. `seed_particles_from_texture` rejection-samples that density into an Array<Particle>. Output flows into `array_feedback.seed`.\n2. **Particle loop** (closes via state, no graph cycle): `array_feedback` holds last frame's sim state, emits as `out`. On `reset_trigger` integer-edge (gated by clip_trigger AND mode==3), reloads from the seed input — the graph-level clear+reseed shape.\n3. **Force-field assembly** (texture-domain math through atoms): `density → gradient_central_diff(scale=UV, wrap=Repeat) → scale_offset_texture(slope_strength * area_scale) → rotate_vec2_by_angle(angle)` replaces the legacy fused gradient/rotate dispatch. `→ gaussian_blur H/V → blurred_force_field`. `radial_burst_force_field` (driven by `inject_burst`'s active/phase/point outputs) produces an impulse force texture for clip-trigger mode 4. `mix(blurred_field, inject_force, Add) → combined_force`.\n4. **Per-particle dispatch chain**: `sample_texture_at_particles(particles, combined_force) → forces` → `anti_clump_particles(particles, density=blurred_density, strength=anti_clump_slider × turbulence_burst)` (density-weighted Brownian kick) → `euler_step_particles(particles, forces, speed)` (frame-rate-normalised step) → `wrap_particles_torus(particles)` (cyclic boundary).\n5. **Splat**: `scatter_particles → resolve_accumulator → density` (full-res for display, fed back through downsample+blur for the next-frame force-field assembly).\n6. **Display**: `density → reinhard_tone_map (intensity = area_scale × 3) → affine_transform (uv_scale = 1/scale) → final_output`.\n\nClip-trigger modes (same outer-card surface as legacy):\n- mode 0 (Turbulence): repurposed to **anti-clump strength burst** — `anti_clump.strength *= 1 + 9*env`. Legacy's noise-advection branch is dropped in the decomposition (its anti-clumping role is now covered explicitly by `anti_clump_particles`). Slider still has an audible effect; underlying mechanism changed.\n- mode 1 (Rot Flip): `rotation_angle += π * env`\n- mode 2 (Flow Inv): `slope_strength *= 1 - 2*env`\n- mode 3 (Pattern): `array_feedback.reset_trigger` edges on clip_trigger AND mode==3 — clear and reseed from the (newly cycled) pattern density texture\n- mode 4 (Inject): `inject_burst` 0.5s state machine drives `radial_burst_force_field` (point, force, envelope, phase)\n\nKnown parity deltas vs legacy:\n(1) Density-adaptive simplex noise advection inside the integrator is dropped — its anti-clumping role is covered by `anti_clump_particles`; visual flow becomes more deterministic (less organic wobble). `turbulence` slider re-targets to anti-clump strength burst on mode 0 rather than noise-amplitude scaling.\n(2) Seed patterns are produced as density textures rejection-sampled by `seed_particles_from_texture` rather than per-particle pattern placement. Particles concentrate in bright regions of the density rather than landing on exact pattern coordinates — visually similar but statistically distributed.\n(3) `visible_count`/excess-particle dead-at-center behaviour is dropped; `fill` slider now multiplies `count_m` to scale `active_count`. Fewer alive particles ↔ smaller buffer ↔ less GPU work.\n(4) Mode-3 pattern cycle still advances on every trigger regardless of mode (legacy did this too).\n(5) Injection burst is added as a force-field texture summed into the velocity field BEFORE Euler integration, rather than as a post-integration position perturbation. Mathematically near-equivalent for small steps.\n\nWhat the decomposition unlocks:\n- Pattern math is JSON-editable WGSL: add an 8th pattern by appending a `case` to the seed_pattern shader switch. AI agents can author novel seed shapes.\n- Each integrator stage (sample, anti-clump, euler, wrap) is a separate atom — swap Euler for Verlet (future sibling atom), or insert a new force-field contribution by wiring into the `mix` upstream of `sample_texture_at_particles`.\n- The radial-burst impulse, gradient, and rotation are reusable building blocks for any future flow-field particle sim.",
